11/05/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- Meeting on Tuesday (10 May), Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski, Montenegrin counterpart Milo Djukanovic and Albanian Deputy Prime Minister Namik Dokle said economic prosperity is the main priority for the region.
A joint declaration issued at the end of their trilateral talks stressed the need for building a modern infrastructure and interconnection in Southeast Europe and reiterated their commitment to completing Pan-European Transport Corridors 8 and 10.
The three officials also expressed satisfaction with efforts against organised crime, particularly trafficking.
(Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 10/05/05)
